      <title>Install Python</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/docs/before-start/install-python/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/docs/before-start/install-python/</guid>
      <description>&lt;h1 id=&#34;install-python&#34;&gt;Install Python&lt;/h1&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;how-to-install-python&#34;&gt;How to install Python&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;There a couple of ways to install Python in your computer:&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;You can go to the official &lt;a href=&#34;https://www.python.org/downloads/&#34;&gt;page&lt;/a&gt;&#xA;and follow the given instructions for your operation system.&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;You can use the &lt;a href=&#34;https://asdf-vm.com&#34;&gt;asdf&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;/ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;validate-python-is-installed&#34;&gt;Validate Python is installed&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Once you have Python installed you should be able to run the following command&#xA;in the terminal:&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-sh&#34; data-lang=&#34;sh&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;python --version &lt;span style=&#34;color:#75715e&#34;&gt;# =&amp;gt; Python 3.12.0&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
