      <guid>http://localhost:1313/docs/before-start/prepare-the-book/</guid>
      <description>&lt;h1 id=&#34;prepare-the-project-for-this-book&#34;&gt;Prepare the project for this book&lt;/h1&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Once we have Python installed we need to create the folders&#xA;structure in which we≈ïe going to write the code for each&#xA;chapter.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;create-the-folder-for-the-chapters-and-its-tests&#34;&gt;Create the folder for the chapters and its tests&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;To do so, we need to create a couple of folders with the&#xA;following command:&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-sh&#34; data-lang=&#34;sh&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;mkdir tests src&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id=&#34;create-a-new-python-project&#34;&gt;Create a new Python project&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;After that we&amp;rsquo;re in position of creating the project using &lt;a href=&#34;https://python-poetry.org&#34;&gt;poetry&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
